## Distance between two points
### Along a line
The distance between two points $A=[x_{1}]$, $B=[x_{2}]$ on a line is equal to the absolute value of the difference of real numbers $x_{1}$ and $x_{2}$.  
$$
|AB| = |x_{1} - x_{2}| = \sqrt{(x_{1} - x_{2})^2}
$$

